~Jatin Lachhani
: FM import numpy as np import matplotlib.pyplot as plt # --------------------------- # User Inputs # --------------------------- Ac = float(input("Enter Carrier Amplitude (Ac): ")) Am = float(input("Enter Message Amplitude (Am): ")) fc = float(input("Enter Carrier Frequency (fc): ")) fm = float(input("Enter Message Frequency (fm): ")) beta = float(input("Enter FM Modulation Index (beta): ")) # --------------------------- # Time Axis # --------------------------- t = np.linspace(0, 1, 5000)  # 1 second duration # --------------------------- # Signals # --------------------------- # Carrier Signal carrier = Ac * np.cos(2 * np.pi * fc * t) # Message Signal message = Am * np.cos(2 * np.pi * fm * t) # FM Modulated Signal fm_signal = Ac * np.cos(2 * np.pi * fc * t + beta * np.sin(2 * np.pi * fm * t)) # --------------------------- # Plotting # --------------------------- plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8)) plt.subplot(3,1,1) plt.plot(t, carrier) plt.title("Carrier Signal c(t)") plt.xlabel("Time") plt.ylabel("Amplitude") plt.grid(True) plt.subplot(3,1,2) plt.plot(t, message) plt.title("Message Signal m(t)") plt.xlabel("Time") plt.ylabel("Amplitude") plt.grid(True) plt.subplot(3,1,3) plt.plot(t, fm_signal) plt.title("FM Modulated Signal s(t)") plt.xlabel("Time") plt.ylabel("Amplitude") plt.grid(True) plt.tight_layout() plt.show()
